{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"c8de41b4-4e3c-4b32-82c4-9393ede0d810","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Wrote design.md, spec.md, and tasks.md under specrunner/changes/archive-ci-structural-detection/. Plan: replace the time-based CI-less inference in job archive --with-merge with structural detection of the archive commit's tree. A new pure module (workflow-ci-detection.ts) inspects .github/workflows/ via local git (ls-tree + cat-file, no GitHub API, no YAML parser) and classifies push/pull_request triggers at the text level with a fail-closed bias. merge-then-archive.ts gates the \"none\"-grace merge on the result: CI-present → keep waiting until mergeWaitTimeoutMs then escalate (fail-closed); CI-less (no workflow or no push/PR trigger) → preserve existing grace→merge behavior; undefined archiveSha / git inspection failure → fail-closed. Scope limited to the change folder; no source edits performed (left to the implementer). BLOCKED_CHECK_GRACE_MS, API-history detection, mergeWaitTimeoutMs default, and paths-filter precision are out of scope per the request.","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-23T09:08:30.238Z","endedAt":"2026-07-23T09:16:03.199Z","commitOid":"bf4a89523de83133e798bdda91370d67ec46738d"}
